-- Obama to Attend Service for Connecticut School Shooting Victims
-- B y   J o e   S o b c z y k
-- 2012-12-16T00:23:16Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-12-16/obama-to-attend-service-for-connecticut-school-shooting-victims.html
President  Barack Obama  will meet
tomorrow with families of the victims of the massacre at a
Newtown, Connecticut, elementary school and speak at a memorial
 service , the White House announced.  The service is scheduled for 7 p.m. local time, the White
House said in a statement.  Twenty children and six adults were killed at the school
yesterday in the town of 28,000 about 60 miles (97 kilometers)
northeast of New York City. The gunman, identified by
authorities as  20-year-old Adam Lanza, killed himself. He also
shot to death his mother before rampage at Sandy Hook Elementary
School.  Obama said yesterday the nation must “come together and
take meaningful action to prevent more tragedies like this
regardless of the politics.”  To contact the reporter on this story:
Joe Sobczyk in Washington at 
 jsobczyk@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Steven Komarow at 
 skomarow1@bloomberg.net  